  "title": "Get state and post to page ",
  "body": "Hi All! We've upgraded from V2 to V3 and hit a snag. Previously, we had a search function on the homepage, we'd grab the state and then on button click we'd then go to another page and show the results. \r\n\r\nNow we've upgraded, when we post to the page, the results aren't showing, instead it doesn't sync. I've been reading the docs and trying to figure out what I've done wrong / or not changed inline with the new version but can't see anything. \r\n\r\nIf anyone can point me in the right direction, that would be a huge help.  \r\n\r\nI've got the following so far:\r\n\r\n    routing: true,\r\n        searchFunction: function(helper) {\r\n        var state = helper.getState(['query', 'attribute:*']);\r\n        var qs = algoliasearchHelper.url.getQueryStringFromState(state);\r\n        $('#search-button').on('click', function(){\r\n            window.location.href = \"/product-page?\" + qs;\r\n        });\r\n        helper.search();\r\n    },",
